    • Constructor Detail

      • User

        public User(int id,
    Incident.Type type,
    java.lang.String nameFirst,
    java.lang.String nameMiddle,
    java.lang.String nameLast,
    UserEventListener... listeners)
        Creates a new User, representing an User entry from the database.
        Parameters:
        id - The automatically-assigned unique integer key of this User.
        type - The user's type (i.e. what sort of Incident they can respond to).
        nameFirst - The user's first (given) name.
        nameMiddle - The user's middle (given) name(s).
        nameLast - The user's last (family) name.
        listeners - A variable-length list of event listeners that will watch this incident's state.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if nameFirst, nameMiddle or nameLast are null.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if id is negative.
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if Computer is used as type (not currently supported).
